{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float.toFloat32\"><span class=\"name\">Float</span>.<span class=\"name\">toFloat32</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float\">Float</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Converts a 64-bit floating-point number to a 32-bit floating-point number.\nThis may lose precision.\n\nThis function does not reduce in the kernel.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float.toFloat32","kind":"opaque","line":527,"name":"Float.toFloat32","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Float32.lean#L527-L533"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.toFloat\"><span class=\"name\">Float32</span>.<span class=\"name\">toFloat</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float.html#Float\">Float</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Converts a 32-bit floating-point number to a 64-bit floating-point number.\n\nThis function does not reduce in the kernel.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.toFloat","kind":"opaque","line":521,"name":"Float32.toFloat","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Float32.lean#L521-L526"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.scaleB\"><span class=\"name\">Float32</span>.<span class=\"name\">scaleB</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">x</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">i</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Data/Int/Basic.html#Int\">Int</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Efficiently computes `x * 2^i`.\n\nThis function does not reduce in the kernel.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.scaleB","kind":"opaque","line":513,"name":"Float32.scaleB","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Float32.lean#L513-L519"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">instance</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#instMaxFloat32\"><span class=\"name\">instMaxFloat32</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Max\">Max</a> <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#instMaxFloat32","kind":"instance","line":511,"name":"instMaxFloat32","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Float32.lean#L511-L511"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">instance</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#instMinFloat32\"><span class=\"name\">instMinFloat32</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Min\">Min</a> <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#instMinFloat32","kind":"instance","line":509,"name":"instMinFloat32","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Float32.lean#L509-L509"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">instance</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#instHomogeneousPowFloat32\"><span class=\"name\">instHomogeneousPowFloat32</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#HomogeneousPow\">HomogeneousPow</a> <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#instHomogeneousPowFloat32","kind":"instance","line":507,"name":"instHomogeneousPowFloat32","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Float32.lean#L507-L507"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.abs\"><span class=\"name\">Float32</span>.<span class=\"name\">abs</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Computes the absolute value of a floating-point number.\n\nThis function has a logical model in terms of `Float32.Model`. It is implemented in compiled code by\nthe C function `fabsf`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.abs","kind":"def","line":498,"name":"Float32.abs","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Float32.lean#L498-L505"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.round\"><span class=\"name\">Float32</span>.<span class=\"name\">round</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Rounds to the nearest integer, rounding away from zero at half-way points.\n\nThis function does not reduce in the kernel. It is implemented in compiled code by the C function\n`roundf`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.round","kind":"opaque","line":491,"name":"Float32.round","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Float32.lean#L491-L497"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.floor\"><span class=\"name\">Float32</span>.<span class=\"name\">floor</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Computes the floor of a floating-point number, which is the largest integer that's no larger\nthan the given number.\n\nThis function does not reduce in the kernel. It is implemented in compiled code by the C function\n`floorf`.\n\nExamples:\n * `Float32.floor 1.5 = 1`\n * `Float32.floor (-1.5) = (-2)`\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.floor","kind":"opaque","line":479,"name":"Float32.floor","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Float32.lean#L479-L490"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.ceil\"><span class=\"name\">Float32</span>.<span class=\"name\">ceil</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Computes the ceiling of a floating-point number, which is the smallest integer that's no smaller\nthan the given number.\n\nThis function does not reduce in the kernel. It is implemented in compiled code by the C function\n`ceilf`.\n\nExamples:\n * `Float32.ceil 1.5 = 2`\n * `Float32.ceil (-1.5) = (-1)`\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.ceil","kind":"opaque","line":467,"name":"Float32.ceil","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Float32.lean#L467-L478"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.cbrt\"><span class=\"name\">Float32</span>.<span class=\"name\">cbrt</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Computes the cube root of a floating-point number.\n\nThis function does not reduce in the kernel. It is implemented in compiled code by the C function\n`cbrtf`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.cbrt","kind":"opaque","line":460,"name":"Float32.cbrt","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Float32.lean#L460-L466"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.sqrt\"><span class=\"name\">Float32</span>.<span class=\"name\">sqrt</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Computes the square root of a floating-point number.\n\nThis function has a logical model in terms of `Float32.Model`. It is implemented in compiled code by\nthe C function `sqrtf`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.sqrt","kind":"def","line":452,"name":"Float32.sqrt","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Float32.lean#L452-L459"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.pow\"><span class=\"name\">Float32</span>.<span class=\"name\">pow</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Raises one floating-point number to the power of another. Typically used via the `^` operator.\n\nThis function does not reduce in the kernel. It is implemented in compiled code by the C function\n`powf`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.pow","kind":"opaque","line":445,"name":"Float32.pow","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Float32.lean#L445-L451"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.log10\"><span class=\"name\">Float32</span>.<span class=\"name\">log10</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Computes the base-10 logarithm of a floating-point number.\n\nThis function does not reduce in the kernel. It is implemented in compiled code by the C function\n`log10f`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.log10","kind":"opaque","line":438,"name":"Float32.log10","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Float32.lean#L438-L444"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.log2\"><span class=\"name\">Float32</span>.<span class=\"name\">log2</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Computes the base-2 logarithm of a floating-point number.\n\nThis function does not reduce in the kernel. It is implemented in compiled code by the C function\n`log2f`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.log2","kind":"opaque","line":431,"name":"Float32.log2","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Float32.lean#L431-L437"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.log\"><span class=\"name\">Float32</span>.<span class=\"name\">log</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Computes the natural logarithm `ln x` of a floating-point number.\n\nThis function does not reduce in the kernel. It is implemented in compiled code by the C function\n`logf`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.log","kind":"opaque","line":424,"name":"Float32.log","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Float32.lean#L424-L430"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.exp2\"><span class=\"name\">Float32</span>.<span class=\"name\">exp2</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Computes the base-2 exponential `2^x` of a floating-point number.\n\nThis function does not reduce in the kernel. It is implemented in compiled code by the C function\n`exp2f`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.exp2","kind":"opaque","line":417,"name":"Float32.exp2","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Float32.lean#L417-L423"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.exp\"><span class=\"name\">Float32</span>.<span class=\"name\">exp</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Computes the exponential `e^x` of a floating-point number.\n\nThis function does not reduce in the kernel. It is implemented in compiled code by the C function\n`expf`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.exp","kind":"opaque","line":410,"name":"Float32.exp","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Float32.lean#L410-L416"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.atanh\"><span class=\"name\">Float32</span>.<span class=\"name\">atanh</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Computes the hyperbolic arc tangent (inverse tangent) of a floating-point number.\n\nThis function does not reduce in the kernel. It is implemented in compiled code by the C function\n`atanhf`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.atanh","kind":"opaque","line":403,"name":"Float32.atanh","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Float32.lean#L403-L409"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.acosh\"><span class=\"name\">Float32</span>.<span class=\"name\">acosh</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Computes the hyperbolic arc cosine (inverse cosine) of a floating-point number.\n\nThis function does not reduce in the kernel. It is implemented in compiled code by the C function\n`acoshf`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.acosh","kind":"opaque","line":396,"name":"Float32.acosh","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Float32.lean#L396-L402"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.asinh\"><span class=\"name\">Float32</span>.<span class=\"name\">asinh</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Computes the hyperbolic arc sine (inverse sine) of a floating-point number.\n\nThis function does not reduce in the kernel. It is implemented in compiled code by the C function\n`asinhf`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.asinh","kind":"opaque","line":389,"name":"Float32.asinh","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Float32.lean#L389-L395"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.tanh\"><span class=\"name\">Float32</span>.<span class=\"name\">tanh</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Computes the hyperbolic tangent of a floating-point number.\n\nThis function does not reduce in the kernel. It is implemented in compiled code by the C function\n`tanhf`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.tanh","kind":"opaque","line":382,"name":"Float32.tanh","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Float32.lean#L382-L388"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.cosh\"><span class=\"name\">Float32</span>.<span class=\"name\">cosh</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Computes the hyperbolic cosine of a floating-point number.\n\nThis function does not reduce in the kernel. It is implemented in compiled code by the C function\n`coshf`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.cosh","kind":"opaque","line":375,"name":"Float32.cosh","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Init/Data/Float/Float32.lean#L375-L381"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32.sinh\"><span class=\"name\">Float32</span>.<span class=\"name\">sinh</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a> → <a href=\"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.html#Float32\">Float32</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Computes the hyperbolic sine of a floating-point number.\n\nThis function does not reduce in the kernel. It is implemented in compiled code by the C function\n`sinhf`.\n","docLink":"./Init/Data/Float/Float32.ht